plt.figure(figsize=(20, 5))

features = ['Indus','Indus','Crim', 'Rm']
target = boston['Medv']

for i, col in enumerate(features):
    plt.subplot(1, len(features) , i+1)
    x = boston[col]
    y = target
    plt.scatter(x, y, marker='o')
    plt.title(col)
    plt.xlabel(col)
    plt.ylabel('House Values')
